<title>SOUTH AFRICA: Guardian yr shr slips, div increased.</title>
<headline>Guardian yr shr slips, div increased.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-02-25</dateline>
<text>
<p>Yr ended December 31, 1996</p>
<p>		(million rand unless stated)</p>
<p>    Shr (cts)			  769.0    vs    800.0</p>
<p>    Div (cts)	 233.0 making 400.0    vs    334.0</p>
<p>    Gross premium income	1,646.52    vs    1,390.00</p>
<p>    Underwriting profit	     6.27    vs    22.30</p>
<p>    Investment income		80.04    vs    69.70</p>
<p>Div payable March 27</p>
<p>On register March 7</p>
<p>Full name: Guardian National Insurance Company Ltd (insurance)</p>
<p>NOTE - The company said the underwriting profit was stated after incurring expenditure of approximately 6.5 million on a new direct and broker affinity distribution channel.</p>
<p>It said a high incidence of corporate fire losses and the extensive floods experienced earl in the year were teh main reasons for the lower level of underwriting profit. It said car theft particularly in Gauteng remained a a cause for concern.</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom +27 11 482 1003</p>
